    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know there are people to talk to, but talking doesnt change the physical reality. it doesnt stop the nerves from firing or the crushing exhaustion. i feel like i've tried everything \"supportive\" and nothing actually fixes the fact that this is my life now. it's just constant. it feels less like a battle i can win and more like a sentence i never asked for. sometimes it feels like the most logical thing in the world would be to just... stop. to just let it be over so the silence finally comes.",
